16/01/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A new parliament speaker will be elected in February, Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski announced on Sunday (15 January), confirming that incumbent Speaker Ljupco Jordanovski has been appointed as Macedonia's new ambassador to the United States.
The mandate of the current ambassador, Nikola Dimitrov, expires in March.
Buckovski said he expects political agreement on a new speaker by mid-February.
(Telma TV, A1 TV, Makfax - 15/01/06)
